Huge Sunny Master Bedroom in heart of Mission Available in 3br/1ba
descr: One of our roommates is moving to Tahoe and we're looking for someone to fill his room. It's a massive master bedroom in a 3 bedroom/1 bath apartment on the top floor of a historic Victorian flat in San Francisco's vibrant Mission District. The room has a beautiful bay window, great sunlight, and two very large closets.The kitchen has a gas range and receives tons of natural light. The living room is also huge and has a 55-inch TV. Bart is less than a block away, and there are countless restaurants, bars, and Taquerias close by. You would be sharing the apartment with two other roommates, both in their mid-twenties, who attended the University of Pennsylvania and both work in tech. Z- He loves to climb, enjoys video games, likes to snowboard, and likes exploring new bars/restaurants.J- He loves to surf, climb, snowboard, and is a general outdoorsman. About you: You have a stable job and income (proof will be requested before lease signing), are between the ages of 22-30, are neat, spend most of your days not working from home, and are not the type to bring the party back to your living space. We're a pretty chill group, but like to have a good time, go out on the weekends, take camping trips, and explore the area. We are looking for someone to move in February 1, 2017. The lease will be month to month, but we would ideally like someone who is looking to stay for at least 6 months. Rent will be $1670, plus utilities. If you are interested, please reply back with a bit about yourself, current employment, why you'd be a good fit, link to FB, Twitter, Linkedin, Instagram etc. Since apartment hunting is a crazy process, the simple "I'm interested, is this room still available?" will be screened out.No couples or animals please. No smoking in the apartment. Good luck, and happy hunting!

Can be used as warehouse space with  car hoists installed for extra parking.The property is larger than any two other properties on Oakridge combined. You can confirm with other realty based web site like z  illow dot comThe house is located at the end of a long secluded and quiet cu-de-sac with friendly neighbors. Very secluded and quiet secure location, most outsiders just dont know the location exist. One road up, one road down. One can take a walk among the trees at night without feeling insecure. Minimal traffic, border with San Bruno Mountain State Park. And only one side of the street is developed, 1/2 the population and double the parking space. The house has true 180 degree + panoramic view of the Bay, the City and even the peninsula.  Very easy commute to 101 and 280, and only minutes to SFSU and City College and SF state. BART station is close by too, but not within walking distance. Each bedroom has : Closet with sliding mirror doors  Large remote control skylight Very efficient and better than code insulation and climate control.  - Washer & dryer with plenty of extra storage spaces and closets. - Spacious Common and Dining area  - Fully equipped kitchen with gas stove, oven, dish washer and granite counter-tops  - High ceilings and genuine hardwood floor throughout. - CCTV / security system installed.Most rooms are twice as large as your average San Francisco apartment room. Ideal for home based business or multiple room mates or large extended family.Rent is for unfurnished , furniture can be supplied for additional cost.Due to past experiences, we can no longer afford to accept section 8. No sub lease on the web like Airnb.com is allowed without written agreement from owner.We also require $50 per applicants to cover the cost of background and credit checks.
